item.title: Contributing
item.description:
Contributing to cem

Thank you for your interest in contributing to cem! This guide will help you set up your environment for development, building, and testing. Please read carefully and reach out if you have questions.

Getting Started

  • Fork and clone the repo: 
    git clone https://github.com/bennypowers/cem.git
cd cem
  • Install Go (version 1.24 or newer recommended).
  • Install Node.js (version 22 recommended) and npm.

Building

Native Build (Linux/macOS)

To build the project for your local architecture:

item.title: Installation
item.description:
For go binaries:

go install bennypowers.dev/cem@latest

For NPM projects:

npm install --save-dev @pwrs/cem

Or clone this repository and build from source:

git clone https://github.com/bennypowers/cem.git
cd cem
make

Shell Completion

cem supports shell completion for Bash, Zsh, Fish, and PowerShell. The completion scripts provide tab completion for commands, flags, and file paths.
